I recently ordered the Chicken Pepperoni Stuffed Garlic Bread from the Domino's app. The delivery was impressively quick, arriving within 20 minutes. However, the Chicken Pepperoni Stuffed Garlic Bread was very disappointing. It was dry inside, containing only pepperoni and a little cheese. The usual gooey, melted cheese that I look forward to was missing, making it very dry to eat.

This raises the question: Is Domino's prioritizing delivery within 30 minutes over the quality of their product? This is the second time I've been disappointed by Domino's in recent times. The product's appearance on the box sets high expectations, but the reality is quite different.
